const e=[{id:"L127-ch-001",type:"choice",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:127,difficulty:"easy",tags:["语法","被动语态","情态动词被动"],block:"grammar",prompt:"情态动词 + 被动语态的结构是什么？",question:"选出正确选项：",options:["情态动词 + be + 过去分词 — It must be done.（必须被做。）The work should be finished today.（工作应该今天被完成。）","情态动词 + been + 过去分词","情态动词 + being + 过去分词","情态动词 + is + 过去分词"],correctIndex:0,explanation:`【情态动词 + 被动语态】结构：can/must/should/may/might + be + 过去分词。情态动词后接动词原形，所以用 be（不是 am/is/are/was/were/been）。
① It must be done.（必须被做）。② The work should be finished today.（工作应该今天被完成）。③ It can be fixed.（它可以被修好）。④ The door may be locked.（门可能被锁了）。
【be 是原形】因为情态动词后永远接动词原形，所以被动语态的 be 保持原形。千万不要写成 must is done ❌ 或 must been done ❌。`},{id:"L127-ch-002",type:"choice",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:127,difficulty:"easy",tags:["词汇","famous/actress/schoolgirl/recognize"],block:"vocabulary",prompt:'"famous", "actress", "schoolgirl" 和 "recognize" 分别是什么意思？',question:"选出正确选项：",options:["famous = 著名的（adj.），actress = 女演员（n.），schoolgirl = 女学生（n.），recognize = 认出（v.）",'四者都表示"学校"',"famous = 失败，actress = 行动，schoolgirl = 学校，recognize = 拒绝","全都是形容词"],correctIndex:0,explanation:"【L127 核心词汇】① famous（adj.）= 著名的：She is a famous actress.（她是一位著名的女演员）。② actress（n.）= 女演员（actor = 男演员，actress = 女演员）。③ schoolgirl（n.）= 女学生（schoolboy = 男学生）。④ recognize（v.）= 认出：She can be recognized easily. → 情态被动：She can be recognized easily.（她很容易被认出）。"},{id:"L127-ch-003",type:"choice",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:127,difficulty:"easy",tags:["词汇","appear/stage/stock"],block:"vocabulary",prompt:'"appear", "stage" 和 "stock" 分别是什么意思？',question:"选出正确选项：",options:["appear = 出现/显得（v. — appear on stage），stage = 舞台（n.），stock = 库存/股票（n. — in stock 有存货）","appear = 消失，stage = 座位，stock = 石头","全都是名词","stock 是动词，appear 是名词"],correctIndex:0,explanation:`【L127-128 核心词汇】① appear（v.）= 出现 / 显得：She appeared on stage.（她出现在舞台上）。appear to be = 似乎/显得。② stage（n.）= 舞台：on the stage（在舞台上）。③ stock（n.）= 库存/存货/股票：in stock（有存货），out of stock（没货了）。
【appear 两种意思】① appear = 出现：A man appeared at the door. ② appear to be = 似乎/显得：He appears to be tired.（他似乎累了 = He seems tired）。`},{id:"L128-ch-001",type:"choice",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:128,difficulty:"medium",tags:["语法","被动语态","must/can推测+被动"],block:"grammar",prompt:`"He can't be recognized." 和 "He must be recognized." 意思有什么不同？`,question:"选出正确选项：",options:[`can't be recognized = 不可能被认出（推测/判断 — 他太变了所以不可能被认出）。must be recognized = 一定被认出 / 必须被认出（must 有两种意思：推测"一定"和必须"必须"）。`,"两者意思完全相同","can't 表示能力，must 表示过去",'两者都表示"必须"'],correctIndex:0,explanation:`【情态动词 + 被动 的双重含义】can't be done = 不可能被...（否定推测 — It can't be done = 这不可能被做成）。must be done = ① 必须被...（义务 — The work must be done today.）② 一定被...（推测 — He must be loved by everyone. 他一定被每个人喜爱）。
【must 两种意思辨别】上下文决定：must be done + 强制性要求 → 必须被...。must be done + 逻辑推断 → 一定被...。
【can be done】① 可以被...（可能性 — It can be done easily.）② 有时被...（一般规律 — The road can be closed in winter. 这条路冬天有时会被封）。`},{id:"L128-ch-002",type:"choice",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:128,difficulty:"medium",tags:["语法","被动语态","情态被动+完成"],block:"grammar",prompt:'"The work must have been finished." 这句话的语法结构是什么？',question:"选出正确选项：",options:['must + have been + 过去分词 — 对过去情况的被动推测"一定已经被完成了"。这是情态动词完成时被动：must have been done。',"must + be + done","must + has been + done","must + had been + done"],correctIndex:0,explanation:`【情态动词完成时被动】结构：must/may/might/could + have been + 过去分词。用于对"过去发生的事"的被动推测。
① The work must have been finished.（工作一定已经被完成了 — 对过去被动的肯定推测）。
② He may have been told the news.（他可能已经被告诉这个消息了）。
③ It can't have been done by him.（这不可能被他做完了 — 否定推测）。
【vs 一般情态被动】must be done（现在/将来被动）vs must have been done（过去被动推测）。have been + done = 被动 + 完成 + 情态 三重结构：must（推测）+ have been（完成时被动助词）+ done（过去分词）。`},{id:"L128-ch-003",type:"choice",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:128,difficulty:"medium",tags:["语法","被动语态","should/ought to被动"],block:"grammar",prompt:'"The garden should be watered every day." 和 "The garden ought to be watered." 有什么不同？',question:"选出正确选项：",options:["should be done 和 ought to be done 基本同义（都应该被...）。should 更常用，ought to 更正式/强调道德义务。两者后都接 be + 过去分词。","should 和 ought to 意思完全相反","ought to be done 是错误语法","should 只能用于主动语态"],correctIndex:0,explanation:`【should vs ought to + 被动】should be done = ought to be done（都应该被做）。区别：should 更常用/口语化，ought to 更正式/强调道德责任。
① The garden should be watered.（花园应该被浇水 — 一般的建议/期望）。
② The garden ought to be watered.（花园理应该被浇水 — 强调"这是对的"这一道德意味）。
【否定】shouldn't be done（不应该被做），oughtn't to be done（不该被做 — 英国英语中较正式，口语中常被 shouldn't 替代）。`},{id:"L128-ch-004",type:"choice",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:128,difficulty:"hard",tags:["语法","被动语态","情态被动综合辨析"],block:"grammar",prompt:"关于情态动词 + 被动语态，以下哪项描述正确？",question:"选出正确选项：",options:["情态动词后永远接动词原形，所以被动结构是 can/must/should + be + done。情态动词可以表达能力（can be done = 能被做）、义务（must be done = 必须被做）、建议（should be done = 应该被做）、推测（must have been done = 一定已经被做了）。","情态动词后接 been 而不是 be","情态动词被动只表示现在","情态动词不能用于被动语态"],correctIndex:0,explanation:`【情态动词被动 四大功能】① 能力/可能性：can be done（能被做）/ can't be done（不可能被做）。② 义务/必须：must be done（必须被做）/ have to be done（必须被做 — 同义）。③ 建议/应当：should be done（应该被做）/ ought to be done（理应该被做）。④ 推测：must have been done（一定已经被做了 — 过去被动推测）/ may have been done（可能已经被做了）。
【情态动词+被动的本质】情态动词给被动动作加了一层"态度/判断"。不是单纯说"被做了"，而是说"能被做、必须被做、应该被做、可能已经被做"。这极大地丰富了被动语态的表达力。`},{id:"L127-fl-001",type:"fill",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:127,difficulty:"easy",tags:["语法","被动语态","情态动词被动填空"],block:"grammar",prompt:"用情态动词 + be + 过去分词填空：",sentence:"The work ___ ___ ___ today. (must be finished) This letter ___ ___ ___ in English. (should be written) The door ___ ___ ___ from the outside. (can be opened) The plants ___ ___ ___ twice a week. (should be watered) The window ___ ___ ___ — it's too high. (cannot be reached)",answer:"must be finished, should be written, can be opened, should be watered, cannot be reached",acceptableAnswers:["must be finished should be written can be opened should be watered cannot be reached","must be finished,should be written,can be opened,should be watered,can not be reached"],hint:"情态动词 + be + 过去分词。must = 必须。should = 应该。can = 可以/能。cannot = 不能。",explanation:`【情态动词被动 五空】① must be finished（必须被完成 — must + be + finished）。② should be written（应该被写 — should + be + written）。③ can be opened（可以被打开 — can + be + opened）。④ should be watered（应该被浇水 — should + be + watered）。⑤ cannot be reached（不可能被够到 — cannot/can't + be + reached）。
【be 形不变】不论主语是单数还是复数，情态动词后的 be 永远是原形：must be done ✅ must is done ❌ must are done ❌。`},{id:"L127-fl-002",type:"fill",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:127,difficulty:"easy",tags:["词汇","课文词汇填空"],block:"vocabulary",prompt:"用 famous, actress, schoolgirl, recognize, appear, stage, stock 填空：",sentence:"She is a ___ ___ who has performed on every major ___ in the country. (famous, actress, stage) As a ___ , she dreamed of becoming a teacher. (schoolgirl) He has changed so much that he cannot be ___ . (recognized) A strange man ___ at the window last night. (appeared) I'm sorry, that item is out of ___ at the moment. (stock)",answer:"famous, actress, stage, schoolgirl, recognized, appeared, stock",acceptableAnswers:["famous actress stage schoolgirl recognized appeared stock","famous,actress,stage,schoolgirl,recognized,appeared,stock"],hint:"著名 = famous。女演员 = actress。舞台 = stage。女学生 = schoolgirl。认出 = recognize。出现 = appear。库存 = stock。",explanation:"【课文词汇七空】① a famous actress（一位著名的女演员 — famous 修饰 actress）。② stage（舞台 — on every major stage = 在每个主要舞台上）。③ schoolgirl（女学生 — as a schoolgirl = 作为女学生时）。④ cannot be recognized（不可能被认出 — 情态被动否定 = can't be done）。⑤ appeared（出现 — appear 过去式 = appeared）。⑥ out of stock（没货了 — in stock 有货，out of stock 没货）。"},{id:"L128-fl-001",type:"fill",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:128,difficulty:"medium",tags:["语法","被动语态","must/can推测被动"],block:"grammar",prompt:"用 must / can't / may + be + 过去分词填空（推测）：",sentence:"He looks so different — he ___ ___ ___ by his old friends. (can't be recognized — 不可能被认出) The garden looks beautiful — it ___ ___ ___ by a professional. (must be maintained — 一定被维护了) I'm not sure, but the letter ___ ___ ___ by tomorrow. (may be delivered — 可能被送达) The noise ___ ___ ___ from upstairs — nobody's up there. (can't be coming — 不可能来自于)",answer:"can't be recognized, must be maintained, may be delivered, can't be coming",acceptableAnswers:["can't be recognized must be maintained may be delivered can't be coming","cannot be recognized,must be maintained,may be delivered,cannot be coming"],hint:"不可能被 → can't be。一定被 → must be。可能被 → may be。推测用情态动词 + be + done。",explanation:`【情态推测被动 四空】① can't be recognized（不可能被认出 — can't + be + done = 否定推测 = 不可能）。② must be maintained（一定被维护了 — must + be + done = 肯定推测 = 一定）。③ may be delivered（可能被送到 — may + be + done = 可能性 = 也许）。④ can't be coming（不可能来自 — can't + be + doing = 正在进行时的推测否定）。
【推测级别 — 从强到弱】must be done（几乎确定）> should be done（很可能）> may/might be done（可能）> could be done（有可能）> can't be done（不可能）。`},{id:"L128-fl-002",type:"fill",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:128,difficulty:"medium",tags:["语法","被动语态","情态完成被动"],block:"grammar",prompt:"用 must / may / could / can't + have been + 过去分词填空（对过去被动推测）：",sentence:"The work is all done — it ___ ___ ___ ___ by a large team. (must have been completed) I don't know for sure, but the letter ___ ___ ___ ___ yesterday. (may have been sent) The window is broken — it ___ ___ ___ ___ by the storm last night. (could have been broken) The secret ___ ___ ___ ___ to him — he knew nothing about it. (can't have been told)",answer:"must have been completed, may have been sent, could have been broken, can't have been told",acceptableAnswers:["must have been completed may have been sent could have been broken can't have been told","must have been completed,may have been sent,could have been broken,cannot have been told"],hint:"一定已经被 → must have been done。可能已经被 → may have been done。可能已经被(弱) → could have been done。不可能已经被 → can't have been done。",explanation:`【情态完成被动 — 对过去的推测】must/may/could/can't + have been + done = 推测过去是否"被做了"。
① must have been completed（一定已经被完成了 — 基于现在的证据"work is all done"做肯定推测）。
② may have been sent（可能已经被寄出了 — 不确定）。
③ could have been broken（有可能被打破了 — could 比 may 更不确定）。
④ can't have been told（不可能已经被告知了 — 基于他什么都不知道的证据做否定推测）。
【结构拆解】must（情态）+ have（完成）+ been（被动）+ done（过去分词）。这是三重语法叠加的最复杂结构之一。`},{id:"L128-fl-003",type:"fill",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:128,difficulty:"medium",tags:["语法","被动语态","主动变情态被动"],block:"grammar",prompt:"将主动句变为情态动词被动语态填空：",sentence:"You must finish the work today. → The work ___ ___ ___ today. (must be finished) We should water the plants every day. → The plants ___ ___ ___ every day. (should be watered) They can fix the problem easily. → The problem ___ ___ ___ easily. (can be fixed) Someone may have stolen the car. → The car ___ ___ ___ ___ . (may have been stolen)",answer:"must be finished, should be watered, can be fixed, may have been stolen",acceptableAnswers:["must be finished should be watered can be fixed may have been stolen","must be finished,should be watered,can be fixed,may have been stolen"],hint:"must do → must be done。should do → should be done。can do → can be done。may have done → may have been done。",explanation:`【主动→情态被动 四句】① must finish → must be finished（主语 the work 变被动主语，finish→finished）。② should water → should be watered（主语 the plants 变被动主语，water→watered）。③ can fix → can be fixed（主语 the problem 变被动主语，fix→fixed）。④ may have stolen → may have been stolen（may have stolen 主动 → may have been stolen 被动 — have stolen → have been stolen）。
【转换公式】情态主动：情态动词 + 动词原形(或 have done) → 情态被动：情态动词 + be done(或 have been done)。关键在于"be"代替原主动动词的位置。`},{id:"L128-fl-004",type:"fill",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:128,difficulty:"hard",tags:["语法","被动语态","多情态被动综合填空"],block:"grammar",prompt:"根据语境用正确的情态被动形式综合填空：",sentence:"The famous actress ___ ___ ___ everywhere she goes. (is recognized — 事实陈述，不用情态) The documents are important — they ___ ___ ___ under any circumstances. (must not be lost — 绝对不能丢失) The old house looks abandoned, but it ___ still ___ ___ once a year. (may be cleaned — 可能被清洁) By this time tomorrow, the work ___ ___ ___ ___ . (should have been finished — 应该已经被完成了) The road is dangerous; it ___ ___ ___ months ago. (should have been repaired — 本该数月前就被修了)",answer:"is recognized, must not be lost, may be cleaned, should have been finished, should have been repaired",acceptableAnswers:["is recognized must not be lost may be cleaned should have been finished should have been repaired","is recognized,must not be lost,may be cleaned,should have been finished,should have been repaired"],hint:"事实=一般现在时被动。绝对禁止=must not be。低可能性=may be。到将来某时=should have been。本应该=should have been（责备）。",explanation:`【多情态综合填空 五空】① is recognized（一般现在时被动 — 事实描述"她被认出" = 常态，不需要情态动词）。② must not be lost（must not + be + done = 绝对不能...被... — 最强烈的禁止/警告）。③ may be cleaned（may + be + done = 可能被清洁 — 不确定的推测）。④ should have been finished（should + have been + done = 到那时应该已经被完成了 — 对将来完成时的期望）。⑤ should have been repaired months ago（should + have been + done = 本应该早就被修了 — 对未发生的过去行为的批评/遗憾 — "should have been done + 过去时间"表示"理应被做而没做"）。
【should have been done 的双重含义】① 期望将来某时已完成 = "应该已经被..."。② 责备过去未发生 = "本应该被...（但没被）" — 通过时间状语判断。`},{id:"L127-tr-001",type:"translate",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:127,difficulty:"easy",tags:["语法","被动语态","情态被动翻译"],block:"grammar",prompt:"请翻译成英文（使用情态动词 + 被动语态）：",sourceText:"这扇门可以从外面被打开。信必须今天被寄出。这些植物应该每天被浇水。",direction:"cn2en",acceptableAnswers:["This door can be opened from the outside. The letter must be sent today. These plants should be watered every day.","This door can be opened from outside. The letter must be posted today. These plants should be watered daily."],keywords:["can be opened","must be sent","should be watered"],explanation:`【情态被动翻译 三句】① 可以被打开 → can be opened（can + be + opened — "可以"= 可能性 = can）。② 必须被寄出 → must be sent（must + be + sent — "必须"= 义务 = must）。③ 应该被浇水 → should be watered（should + be + watered — "应该"= 建议 = should）。
【情态动词对照】可以/能 → can。必须 → must。应该 → should。可能 → may/might。`},{id:"L127-tr-002",type:"translate",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:127,difficulty:"easy",tags:["词汇","课文词汇翻译"],block:"vocabulary",prompt:"请翻译成英文（使用课文词汇）：",sourceText:"那位著名的女演员出现在舞台上时立刻被认出来了。抱歉，这款商品目前没有库存。她小时候只是个普通的女学生，现在却成了明星。",direction:"cn2en",acceptableAnswers:["The famous actress was recognized immediately when she appeared on the stage. Sorry, this item is out of stock at the moment. She was just an ordinary schoolgirl when she was young, but now she has become a star.","When the famous actress appeared on stage, she was immediately recognized. Sorry, this product is currently out of stock. She was only a normal schoolgirl as a child, but now she is a star."],keywords:["famous","actress","recognized","appeared","stage","stock","out of stock","schoolgirl"],explanation:'【课文词汇翻译 三句】① 被认出来了 → was recognized（过去时被动 — "被认出"是被动语态 — recognize 的过去分词）。出现在舞台上 → appeared on the stage（appear + on stage = 出现在舞台上）。② 没有库存 → out of stock（out of + 名词 = 没有了 — out of stock 固定搭配）。③ 普通的女学生 → an ordinary schoolgirl（schoolgirl 可数名词 — 前面需要冠词）。'},{id:"L128-tr-001",type:"translate",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:128,difficulty:"medium",tags:["语法","被动语态","推测情态被动翻译"],block:"grammar",prompt:"请翻译成英文（使用情态动词的推测被动）：",sourceText:"他变了很多——他不可能被老朋友认出来。花园很漂亮——它一定被专业园丁维护着。工作全做完了——它一定被一个很棒的团队完成了。",direction:"cn2en",acceptableAnswers:["He has changed so much — he can't be recognized by his old friends. The garden is beautiful — it must be maintained by a professional gardener. The work is all done — it must have been completed by a great team.","He has changed a lot — he cannot be recognized by his old friends. The garden looks beautiful — it must be looked after by a professional gardener. All the work is finished — it must have been done by a great team."],keywords:["can't be recognized","must be maintained","must have been completed"],explanation:`【推测情态被动翻译 三句】① 不可能被认出 → can't be recognized（can't = 不可能 — 否定推测 + 被动 — "变得认不出" = "不可能被认出"的英文表达方式）。② 一定被...维护着 → must be maintained（must = 一定 — 肯定推测 + 被动 — 基于"花园很漂亮"这个证据做的推测）。③ 一定已经被完成了 → must have been completed（must + have been + done = 对过去的肯定推测被动 — "一定已经被..."）。
【推测递进】不可能被(can't be) < 可能被(may be) < 一定被(must be) < 一定已经被(must have been)。中文"一定"覆盖现在和过去，英文需要区分 must be done（现在推测）和 must have been done（过去推测）。`},{id:"L128-tr-002",type:"translate",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:128,difficulty:"medium",tags:["语法","被动语态","should have been done翻译"],block:"grammar",prompt:"请翻译成英文（使用 should have been done 表达遗憾/批评）：",sourceText:"这封信本该昨天就被寄出的。这些错误本应该在打印前就被检查出来的。这条路几个月前就该被修了，但到现在还没有。",direction:"cn2en",acceptableAnswers:["This letter should have been sent yesterday. These mistakes should have been checked before printing. This road should have been repaired months ago, but it still hasn't been done.","This letter ought to have been sent yesterday. These errors should have been caught before printing. This road should have been fixed months ago, but it hasn't been yet."],keywords:["should have been sent","should have been checked","should have been repaired"],explanation:`【should have been done = 本应该被...（但没被）】中文"本该"= "应该被做过但实际没被做"的遗憾/批评。英文用 should have been + 过去分词：

① 本该昨天被寄出 → should have been sent yesterday（sent 寄出 — 但实际没寄出 ❌）。
② 本应该在打印前被检查出来 → should have been checked before printing（checked 检查 — 但实际没被检查出来 ❌）。
③ 几个月前就该被修了 → should have been repaired months ago（repaired 修 — 但到现在还没修 ❌ — still hasn't been done）。

【should have been done 的情感色彩】表达对未发生的被动事件的遗憾、批评、懊悔。"这件事理应被做，但不幸没被做。"`},{id:"L128-tr-003",type:"translate",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:128,difficulty:"hard",tags:["语法","被动语态","综合情态被动翻译"],block:"grammar",prompt:"请翻译成英文（综合多种情态被动）：",sourceText:"这个博物馆可以在线被参观，但门票必须在入口处被扫描。游客应该被告知规则。闪光灯不能被使用，因为珍贵的画作可能被损坏。这个规定一定被制定出来是有原因的——每一幅画都必须被保护。历史应该被每个人了解和尊重。这个博物馆在过去的二十年间一直被精心维护着。它被认为是我们城市最宝贵的文化财富之一，必须被世世代代地珍惜。",direction:"cn2en",acceptableAnswers:["This museum can be visited online, but tickets must be scanned at the entrance. Visitors should be told about the rules. Flash photography cannot be used because the valuable paintings may be damaged. This rule must have been made for a reason — every painting must be protected. History should be known and respected by everyone. This museum has been carefully maintained over the past twenty years. It is considered one of the most valuable cultural treasures of our city and must be cherished for generations.","This museum can be visited online, but tickets have to be scanned at the entrance. Visitors should be informed of the rules. Flash cannot be used as the precious paintings might be damaged. This rule must have been created for a reason — every painting has to be protected. History should be known and respected by all. This museum has been well maintained for the past twenty years. It is regarded as one of our city's most precious cultural assets and must be treasured for generations to come."],keywords:["can be visited","must be scanned","should be told","cannot be used","may be damaged","must have been made","must be protected","should be known","has been maintained","is considered","must be cherished"],explanation:`【综合情态被动翻译 — 博物馆场景】这是一段结合多种情态被动的规则说明与价值阐述：

① 可以在线被参观 → can be visited online（can = 可能性/能力 — 表示"有这种技术可能"）。
② 必须在入口处被扫描 → must be scanned at the entrance（must = 必须/强制性要求）。
③ 应该被告知规则 → should be told about the rules（should = 应该/建议 — "被告诉" = be told — tell→told）。
④ 不能被使用 → cannot be used（cannot = 不允许/不可能 — 禁令）。
⑤ 可能被损坏 → may/might be damaged（may = 可能 — 低确定性推测 — 画作可能受损是风险）。
⑥ 一定被制定出来 → must have been made（must have been done = 对过去的肯定推测 — "制定规则"发生在过去，用 must have been done）。
⑦ 必须被保护 → must be protected（must = 必须 — 义务/必要性）。
⑧ 应该被了解和尊重 → should be known and respected（should = 应该 — 价值观建议 — 主语 history 是不可以自己做"了解"和"尊重"的 — 必须用被动）。
⑨ 一直被精心维护 → has been carefully maintained（现在完成时被动 — over the past twenty years = 从过去持续到现在）。
⑩ 被认为 → is considered（一般现在时被动 — "被认为"是"被看作"的英文表达）。
⑪ 必须被世世代代珍惜 → must be cherished for generations（must = 必须 — 强烈的价值表达 + 被动 = "被珍惜"）。

【情态被动的功能层次】这篇翻译展示了情态被动从"规则"到"价值"的递进：规章制度（must/cannot）→ 风险预防（may be damaged）→ 历史推理（must have been made）→ 价值呼吁（should be known, must be cherished）。情态动词赋予了被动语态不同层次的态度和情感。`},{id:"L127-ro-001",type:"reorder",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:127,difficulty:"easy",tags:["语法","被动语态","情态被动语序"],block:"grammar",prompt:"排列成正确的情态被动语态句子：",words:["The","work","must","be","finished","today","."],correctOrder:[0,1,2,3,4,5,6],correctSentence:"The work must be finished today.",explanation:`【情态被动 语序】主语 + 情态动词 + be + 过去分词 + 时间状语。
【结构】The → work → must → be → finished → today。
【分析】must be finished = 必须被完成。must 情态动词 + be 原形 + finished 过去分词。today 时间状语。`},{id:"L127-ro-002",type:"reorder",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:127,difficulty:"easy",tags:["词汇","课文句子语序"],block:"sentence",prompt:"排列成正确的句子（含课文词汇）：",words:["The","famous","actress","can","be","recognized","easily","."],correctOrder:[0,1,2,3,4,5,6,7],correctSentence:"The famous actress can be recognized easily.",explanation:`【课文句子 语序】主语 + 情态动词 + be + 过去分词 + 副词。
【结构】The → famous → actress → can → be → recognized → easily。
【分析】can be recognized = 可以被认出（情态被动）。easily = 容易地（副词修饰 recognized）。`},{id:"L128-ro-001",type:"reorder",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:128,difficulty:"medium",tags:["语法","被动语态","情态完成被动语序"],block:"grammar",prompt:"排列成情态动词完成时被动语态的句子：",words:["The","letter","must","have","been","sent","yesterday","."],correctOrder:[0,1,2,3,4,5,6,7],correctSentence:"The letter must have been sent yesterday.",explanation:`【情态完成被动 语序】主语 + 情态动词 + have + been + 过去分词 + 时间状语。
【结构】The → letter → must → have → been → sent → yesterday。
【分析】must have been sent = 一定已经被寄出了。must（推测）+ have（完成）+ been（被动）+ sent（过去分词）。yesterday 暗示"被寄出"的动作是昨天完成的。`},{id:"L128-ro-002",type:"reorder",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:128,difficulty:"hard",tags:["语法","被动语态","should have been done语序"],block:"grammar",prompt:"排列成含 should have been done（遗憾）的句子：",words:["The","road","should","have","been","repaired","months","ago","."],correctOrder:[0,1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8],correctSentence:"The road should have been repaired months ago.",explanation:`【should have been done 语序】主语 + should + have + been + 过去分词 + 时间状语。
【结构】The → road → should → have → been → repaired → months → ago。
【分析】should have been repaired = 本应该被修（但没被修）。months ago = 好几个月前（本应在那时被修的时间参照点）。should（应该）+ have been（完成被动）+ repaired（过去分词）= 对"没有被修"这一事实的批评/遗憾。`},{id:"L127-li-001",type:"listening",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:127,difficulty:"easy",tags:["听力","被动语态","认明星场景"],block:"listening",prompt:"听音频，选出这位女士为什么不想被认出来：",audioSrc:"/audio/lesson-127-128.m4a",transcript:"Friend: Look at that woman over there. She must be someone famous. Companion: Why do you say that? Friend: She's wearing sunglasses indoors, and a big hat. Her face can't be seen clearly. Companion: Maybe she just wants to be left alone. Friend: Or maybe she has to be protected from fans. Look — there's a man standing near her. He must be her bodyguard. Companion: You're right. She can be recognized by her voice though. I think I've heard it before. Friend: Wait — isn't that the actress from that new film? Companion: Which one? Friend: The one that was released last month. She played the schoolgirl who appears on stage in the final scene. Companion: Yes! She must be recognized everywhere she goes. No wonder she has to be hidden like that. Friend: It must be difficult — to be watched all the time, every move being recorded by strangers. Companion: I guess that's the price of being famous. Everything you do can be seen and can be judged.",question:"为什么这位女士的脸不容易被看清？",options:["她戴着墨镜和大帽子——她的脸不能被看清楚（her face can't be seen clearly, she has to be protected from fans）","她长得太普通了","周围太暗了","她故意遮住脸不想让朋友看见"],correctIndex:0,explanation:`【明星场景 — 情态被动听辨】对话展示了情态被动在"推测+被动"中的使用：① She must be someone famous（她一定是某位名人 — must be 推测）。② Her face can't be seen clearly（她的脸不能被看清楚 — can't be done 不可能被...）。③ she has to be protected from fans（她必须被保护免受粉丝打扰 — has to be done 必须被...）。④ She can be recognized by her voice（她可以通过声音被认出 — can be done 可以被...）。⑤ the film that was released last month（上个月被发布的电影 — 过去时被动）。⑥ She must be recognized everywhere she goes（她一定到处被认出 — must be done 推测+被动）。⑦ she has to be hidden like that（她必须那样被隐藏起来）。⑧ to be watched all the time（一直被人看着 — 不定式被动）。⑨ every move being recorded by strangers（每个动作都被陌生人记录着 — being done = 现在分词被动）。⑩ Everything you do can be seen and can be judged（你做的每件事都可以被看到和被评判 — can be done 双重）。`},{id:"L127-li-002",type:"listening",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:127,difficulty:"medium",tags:["听力","被动语态","排练场景"],block:"listening",prompt:"听音频，选出排练前哪些事必须被完成：",audioSrc:"/audio/lesson-127-128.m4a",transcript:"Director: Alright everyone, before we start the rehearsal, a few things must be checked. Stage Manager: The lights have already been set. They can be adjusted if needed. Director: Good. The props? Have they been placed correctly? Stage Manager: They should be checked again. Some of them may have been moved. Director: The sound system must be tested before we begin. It must not be forgotten again like last time. Stage Manager: Understood. It will be tested right now. Director: And the script changes — have they been given to all the actors? Stage Manager: They were distributed this morning. Everyone should be informed by now. Director: What about the actress who plays the lead? Has she been told about the new scene? Stage Manager: She was called, but she hasn't been reached yet. A message has been left. Director: She must be found before the rehearsal starts. Her part can't be skipped. Stage Manager: I'll try again. She should be here by now — she was expected at least ten minutes ago. Director: Well, the show must go on. Everything else can be prepared while we wait.",question:"导演说哪些事必须在排练前被做？",options:["灯光可以被调整，道具应该被再次检查，音响系统必须被测试，女主角必须被找到（lights can be adjusted, props should be checked, the sound system must be tested, the actress must be found）","只需要检查灯光","只需要调试音响","不需要准备任何东西"],correctIndex:0,explanation:"【排练场景 — 情态被动听辨】导演的指令和舞台监督的汇报大量使用情态被动语态：① a few things must be checked（一些事情必须被检查 — must be done）。② They can be adjusted（它们可以被调整 — can be done）。③ Have they been placed correctly?（它们被正确放置了吗？— 现在完成时被动）。④ They should be checked again（它们应该被再次检查 — should be done）。⑤ Some of them may have been moved（其中一些可能已经被移动了 — may have been done）。⑥ The sound system must be tested（音响系统必须被测试 — must be done）。⑦ It must not be forgotten again（这绝不能被再次忘记 — must not be done）。⑧ it will be tested（它会被测试 — 将来被动）。⑨ have they been given to all the actors?（它们已经被给所有演员了吗？— 现在完成时被动）。⑩ They were distributed（它们被分发了 — 过去时被动）。⑪ Everyone should be informed（每个人都应该被告知 — should be done）。⑫ Has she been told about...?（她已经被告诉关于...了吗？— 现在完成时被动）。⑬ She was called（她被打了电话 — 过去时被动）。⑭ she hasn't been reached yet（她还没有被联系上 — 现在完成时被动否定）。⑮ A message has been left（一条信息已经被留下）。⑯ She must be found（她必须被找到 — must be done）。⑰ Her part can't be skipped（她的戏份不能被跳过 — can't be done）。⑱ she was expected...（她被期待... — 过去时被动）。⑲ Everything else can be prepared（其他一切可以被准备 — can be done）。"},{id:"L128-li-001",type:"listening",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:128,difficulty:"medium",tags:["听力","被动语态","库存管理场景"],block:"listening",prompt:"听音频，选出什么商品缺货了以及怎么处理：",audioSrc:"/audio/lesson-127-128.m4a",transcript:"Customer: Excuse me, I'm looking for the wooden chairs that were displayed in the window. Assistant: I'm sorry, but those chairs are out of stock at the moment. Customer: Out of stock? But they were here last week. Assistant: Yes, they were very popular. The entire stock was sold within two days. Customer: So can they be ordered? Assistant: Yes, they can be ordered online. More stock should be delivered by next Friday. Customer: Will I be notified when they arrive? Assistant: Of course. Your email address will be taken, and a notification will be sent as soon as the chairs are back in stock. Customer: Can the delivery be arranged for a Saturday? Assistant: Saturday deliveries can be requested. There is an extra charge, but it can be added to your order. Customer: That's fine. And the price — has it been confirmed? Assistant: Yes, the price has been fixed. It won't be changed before your order is placed. Customer: Great. So everything can be sorted out now? Assistant: Absolutely. Your order can be placed right now if you're ready. Customer: Let's do it. I've been looking for chairs like these for months. They must be meant for me!",question:"椅子为什么没有了？怎么可以再买到？",options:["它们脱销了——整批库存在两天内被卖光了。可以在线被订购，下周五之前应该被送到（they are out of stock, the entire stock was sold in two days, they can be ordered online, more stock should be delivered by next Friday）","它们被撤回厂家了","商店关门了","这款椅子停产了"],correctIndex:0,explanation:`【库存管理场景 — 情态+被动听辨】购物对话中被动语态的使用非常密集：① the chairs that were displayed（被展示在橱窗里的椅子 — 过去时被动定语从句）。② those chairs are out of stock（缺货 — 固定表达）。③ The entire stock was sold（整批库存被卖光 — 过去时被动）。④ can they be ordered?（它们可以被订购吗？— 情态被动疑问）。⑤ they can be ordered online（它们可以被在线订购）。⑥ More stock should be delivered（更多库存应该被送到 — should be done）。⑦ Will I be notified?（我会被通知吗？— 将来被动）。⑧ Your email address will be taken（你的邮箱地址会被记下 — 将来被动）。⑨ a notification will be sent（通知会被发出）。⑩ Can the delivery be arranged...?（送货可以被安排吗？— 情态被动疑问）。⑪ Saturday deliveries can be requested（周六送货可以被请求）。⑫ it can be added to your order（它可以被加到你的订单中）。⑬ has it been confirmed?（它已经被确认了吗？— 现在完成时被动）。⑭ the price has been fixed（价格已经被确定了 — 现在完成时被动）。⑮ It won't be changed（它不会被改变 — 将来被动否定）。⑯ everything can be sorted out now?（一切都可以被解决了吗？）。⑰ Your order can be placed（你的订单可以被下了）。⑱ I've been looking for...（我一直在找... — 现在完成时进行时主动）。⑲ They must be meant for me!（它们一定是为我准备的！— must be done = 推测被动 — "一定是被安排的"）。`},{id:"L128-li-002",type:"listening",lessonGroup:"lesson-127-128",lessonNumber:128,difficulty:"hard",tags:["听力","被动语态","综合听力理解"],block:"listening",prompt:"听完整音频，选出有关剧院的故事中什么是正确的：",audioSrc:"/audio/lesson-127-128.m4a",transcript:"Narrator: The old theatre stood at the end of the high street. It had been built in 1890, and for over a hundred years, it had been loved by generations of townspeople. But by the time I first saw it, it had been closed for nearly a decade. The windows were boarded up. The stage had not been walked on. The seats had not been sat in. It was said that the theatre could not be saved — that it must be torn down to make room for new buildings. But a group of us believed something different. We believed that the theatre could be restored, that it should be given a second chance. A campaign was started. Letters were written. Money was raised. And slowly, permission was granted. The work that had to be done was enormous. The roof had to be replaced. The floors had to be strengthened. Every piece of wood had to be treated. The old curtains, which had been eaten by moths, had to be remade by hand. But we never gave up. We knew that this theatre must be saved — not just for us, but for the children who would one day sit in those seats and watch stories come to life on that stage. It took three years. But finally, the day came when the theatre could be reopened. On that night, a famous actress who had grown up in our town came to perform. She said that she had been told about our work and that she simply had to be part of the first performance. When she stepped onto the stage, the audience fell silent. And then she spoke. 'This theatre,' she said, 'should have been lost. By every measure, it should have been forgotten. But it wasn't. It was remembered. It was fought for. And now it can be enjoyed by a new generation.' The applause that followed can still be heard in my memory. What had been broken had been fixed. What had been forgotten had been remembered. And what had been given up for lost had been brought back to life. The old theatre still stands today. It is still loved. And it always will be — as long as there are people who believe that some things simply must be saved.",question:"这座老剧院经历了什么？",options:["它建于1890年，曾关闭了近十年，本应被拆除但被一群市民拯救了——经过三年的修复，它重新开放了，现在仍然被爱着（it was built in 1890, had been closed for a decade, should have been lost, was saved, was restored, reopened, still loved）","它一直被很好地维护，从未关闭","它被拆除了改建成了商场","它被卖给了外国公司"],correctIndex:0,explanation:`【综合听力理解 — 拯救老剧院：被动语态的力量】这是一个"被拯救/被修复/被重新爱"的感人故事，被动语态是这篇叙事最核心的语法手段：

① It had been built in 1890（它被建于1890年 — 过去完成时被动）。② it had been loved by generations（它被几代人爱着 — 过去完成时被动）。③ it had been closed for nearly a decade（它已被关闭近十年 — 过去完成时被动）。④ The stage had not been walked on（舞台没有被走过 — 过去完成时被动否定）。⑤ The seats had not been sat in（座位没有被坐过）。⑥ It was said that...（据说... — 过去时被动 — it is said = 据说）。⑦ the theatre could not be saved（剧院不能被挽救 — 情态被动否定）。⑧ it must be torn down（它必须被拆除 — must be done）。⑨ the theatre could be restored（剧院可以被修复 — could be done）。⑩ it should be given a second chance（它应该被给予第二次机会 — should be done）。⑪ A campaign was started（一场运动被发起 — 过去时被动）。⑫ Letters were written（信被写）。⑬ Money was raised（钱被筹集）。⑭ permission was granted（许可被批准）。⑮ The work had to be done（这项工作必须被完成 — had to be done）。⑯ The roof had to be replaced（屋顶必须被更换）。⑰ The floors had to be strengthened（地板必须被加固）。⑱ Every piece of wood had to be treated（每块木头必须被处理）。⑲ The old curtains had to be remade by hand（旧窗帘必须被手工重新制作）。⑳ this theatre must be saved（这座剧院必须被拯救）。㉑ the theatre could be reopened（剧院可以被重新开放）。㉒ she had been told about our work（她已被告知我们的工作 — 过去完成时被动）。㉓ This theatre should have been lost（这座剧院本应该已经被遗弃了 — should have been done 本应被...而没有被）。㉔ it should have been forgotten（它本应已被遗忘）。㉕ It was remembered（它被记住了）。㉖ It was fought for（它被为它而战了 — fight for 的被动 = be fought for）。㉗ it can be enjoyed by a new generation（它可以被新一代享受 — can be done）。㉘ What had been broken had been fixed（曾被打碎的已被修复 — 过去完成时被动 x2）。㉙ What had been forgotten had been remembered（曾被遗忘的已被记住）。㉚ what had been given up for lost had been brought back to life（曾被放弃的已被带回生命 — 过去完成时被动 x2）。㉛ It is still loved.（它仍然被爱着）。㉜ it always will be（它永远会被爱着 — will be loved 后半省略）。㉝ some things simply must be saved（有些事物必须被拯救 — must be done）。

【33处被动语态】这篇听力是被动语态的巅峰展示。被动语态在这里完成了一项只有它才能完成的叙事任务：让"剧院"始终是主语和情感中心。"谁建了它""谁爱它""谁修复它"这些信息都不重要——重要的是剧院所经历的一切：被建造、被爱、被关闭、被遗弃、被战斗、被修复、被重新开放、被继续爱着。被动语态让一座建筑成为了一篇英雄叙事的主角。`}];export{e as lesson127128Questions};
